              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed using the TUNL",
                "duoplasmatron ion source and 10-MV FN tandem Van de",
                "Graaff accelerator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Natural Ca target was produced by thermal evaporation",
                "of natural metallic calcium onto a 38 mu-g/cm2 thick",
                "natural carbon foil. Rutherford backscattering",
                "revealed that calcium target was composed of 58.3",
                "mu-g/cm2 of Ca, 37.7 mu-g/cm2 of O, 37.8 mu-g/cm2 of",
                "C, and 0.9 mu-g/cm2 S."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The light reaction products were momentum",
                "analyzed by the TUNL high resolution Enge split-pole",
                "magnetic spectrograph, whose total solid angle",
                "acceptance was set to 1 msr. The charged particles",
                "were dispersed by the spectrograph according to their",
                "momenta and were focused onto the spectrograph's",
                "focal plane. A high resolution position sensitive",
                "focal plane detector was deployed. Identification of",
                "a particles was carried out by measuring their energy",
                "losses, residual energies, and positions along the",
                "focal plane of the spectrograph."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Particles detected in spectrometer focal plane",
                "were identified using E-dE method.",
                "Inverse kinematics was used"
              ]
            }
